{"TopicId":219922,"ForumId":144,"TopicTitle":"Borderless Mode Doesn\u0027t Work in KSP2","CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-16T10:25:56Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-16T10:25:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.4.1 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0i9 9900K | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A03070ti | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EIssue 1: BORDERLESS Not Working.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBORDERLESS\u0027s Observed behavior:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nIf KSP2\u0027s resolution is less than Window 10s current resolution, it will be stretched out to fill the screen.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nIt will act like its FULLSCREEN not allowing the player to move their mouse pointer to another screen\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nIt will act like its FULLSCREEN when Alt Tabbing, vanishing/minimizing KSP2\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EWINDOWED\u0027s Observed Behavior:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nReflects the set resolution as a window within\u00A0Windows 10\u0027s bigger resolution\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nIt allows the mouse pointer to move outside KSP2\u0027s window and to the other monitor\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nIt never minimizes/disappears when using Alt Tab.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVideo Evidence:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://youtu.be/yB5gLv_UttM\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://youtu.be/yB5gLv_UttM\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EReplication Steps for 1440p:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nHave Windows 10 at a resolution of 2560x1440 (native)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nChange to \u003Cstrong\u003EWINDOWED \u003C/strong\u003EMode\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nChange to minimum resolution (1280x720)\u003Cstrong\u003E (Note that OBS didn\u0027t pick this up but it did happen)\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nChange to \u003Cstrong\u003EBORDERLESS \u003C/strong\u003E(\u003Cstrong\u003ENote\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E1280x720 is stretched to 2560x1440. Also Note the lack of Monitor changing actual resolution (That comes with screen flickering)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nChange to \u003Cstrong\u003EWINDOWED \u003C/strong\u003EMode (Its appears to be 1280x720 without stretching \u002B having the title bar)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nChange back to \u003Cstrong\u003EBORDERLESS \u003C/strong\u003E(\u003Cstrong\u003ENote \u003C/strong\u003Emouse pointer is trapped within KSP2 screen and not being able to move to the other screen which is on the right)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nIn \u003Cstrong\u003EBORDERLESS \u003C/strong\u003EUse Alt-Tab to lose and gain focus on KSP2 (\u003Cstrong\u003ENote \u003C/strong\u003EKSP2 minimizes/disappear and then pops back up after returning focus)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nNote towards the end of the video \u003Cstrong\u003EWINDOWED \u003C/strong\u003EMode not being affected by Alt-Tab\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EWork Around:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAdd the following to the Launch Options within Steam and also to shortcuts that point to the executable:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n-popupwindow\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSet KSP2 to WINDOWED Mode\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EConclusion:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nBORDERLESS should be identical to WINDOWED but without the title bar or the ability to be dragged.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EIssue 2: Setting to BORDERLESS and Restarting KSP2 is Forced to be FULLSCREEN.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003ESteps to Replicate:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSet to BORDERLESS\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nExit out of the settings screen (this is when the settings config file is updated)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nRestart KSP2 and it\u0027s been changed to FULLSCREEN\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EOther Bug Reports Relating to this:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022224410\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9099089508\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/217871-borderless-mode-does-nothing/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:194px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022226592\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6502398500\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/217900-borderless-game-screen-mode-not-respected-on-launch/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:194px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022227013\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5584830941\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/218719-full-screen-borderless-windowed-settings-not-being-respected-when-window-in-focus/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:194px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-10-16T21:50:20Z\u0022 title=\u002210/16/2023 09:50  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Oct 16\u0022\u003EOctober 16, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Joker58th","CreatedById":178441,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-28T19:36:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.5 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0i7-12700K | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Nvidia GeForce RTX 2080 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe borderless setting does not seem to save to the settings.json file.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSteps to reproduce:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNote FullScreenMode in settings.json file.\u00A0 (Unless you are already in Windowed mode, it will be ExclusiveFullScreen)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLaunch game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSet Game Screen Mode to Borderless and exit settings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNote settings.json file still says\u00A0ExclusiveFullScreen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExiting the game after making the change does not work either.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNote: Windowed mode \u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Edoes \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003Esave and work as expected.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I edit the settings.json file with the \u0022Borderless\u0022 setting, it does work the first time the game is launched.\u00A0 It will then revert back to ExclusiveFullScreen after the game is loaded.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if the problem is related to my monitor\u0027s native resolution, which is higher than the max 2560x1440 in settings?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-11-30T02:53:22Z\u0022 title=\u002211/30/2023 02:53  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Nov 30\u0022\u003ENovember 30, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by The Space Peacock\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-01T16:46:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt doesn\u0027t work as such, known issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheck the third to last post here for a workaround\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed128394100\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/215166-how-to-prevent-ksp2-from-minimizing-when-focus-is-lost-while-in-fullscreen-or-borderless-modes/?do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4334146\u0026amp;embedComment=4334146\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:287px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Joker58th","CreatedById":178441,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-01T18:23:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice work around.\u00A0 \u00A0Thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-04T16:57:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/178441-joker58th/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022178441\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/178441-joker58th/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Joker58th\u003C/a\u003E, merged your bug report.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anonymous Bug Reporter","CreatedById":231013,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-23T00:16:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Intel Core i7 11th Gen | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0RTX 3070 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBorderless window setting has no difference with fullscreen, if I click on any other monitor or press the windows key, the game disapear just as in fullscreen mode\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JebJr","CreatedById":227013,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-03-12T22:08:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCurrent version 0.2.1.0 still experiencing this issue. Windowed mode visible when not in focus, borderless self-minimizes when out of focus.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso unable to get workaround to work when appending --popupwindow to Launch Options in Steam or the target of a manually created Windows shorcut.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-03-12T22:14:29Z\u0022 title=\u002203/12/2024 10:14  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Mar 12\u0022\u003EMarch 12\u003C/time\u003E by JebJr\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}